Source:  Diary
Author:  WILSON
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote:  [Central Otago - Wakatipu : (cf <i>creek</i>) NB not <i>wee</i>] Below us to the East the creek, a small tiny burn, rushes and tears away over crags and stones making a great noise evidently trying hard to make itself important, ... and so down to Mataura.
