Author:  HISLOP
Vol / Page:  20
Edition:
Quote:  There are now several bonnie burns coming down the mountain sides to the river, the largest of which are the famous Roaring Meg and Gentle Annie; and a visitor ... may wash his colours of gold from almost anywhere while his wee wife boils the billy. <i>Ibid.</i> 69 I was invited ... to stop the weekend [near Cromwell], and as Donald was going out ... to try the wash in a nearby burn, I thought it a great idea.
Notes:   [local]

